            "title": "Ørsted Sells Majority Stake in Taiwanese Offshore Wind Farm to Cathay",
            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\">\n        \n                    Danish energy company Ørsted has signed an agreement with Cathay Life Insurance and Cathay Power to sell a 55 percent stake in the Greater Changhua 2 offshore wind farm in Taiwan, which has a capacity of 632 megawatts. The stake is valued at approximately 5 billion Danish kroner, taking into account existing project financing, according to a press release.\n<br/><br/>\n\nThe facility consists of an already operational section and another part currently under construction, which is expected to enter commercial operation in the third quarter of 2026, at which point the transaction is also scheduled to be finalized.\n<br/><br/>\n\nØrsted will retain responsibility for long-term operations and maintenance, and states that through this deal, the company is moving closer to its goal of securing over 35 billion Danish kroner in divestment proceeds during 2025–2026.\n\n    \n    </div>",
